President Donald Trump delivered remarks at the March for Life rally in Washington, D.C., becoming the first sitting president to attend the event. He spoke about defending the right to life for every child, born and unborn, and praised the tens of thousands of high school and college students who attended the rally. Trump highlighted his administration's actions to support pro-life policies, such as reinstating and expanding the Mexico City Policy and appointing conservative federal judges. He also criticized Democrats for their support of late-term abortion and highlighted the need to pass legislation prohibiting it. Trump thanked the women in attendance for their devotion and leadership in the pro-life movement, declaring that mothers are heroes. He concluded his remarks by emphasizing the value and sanctity of every human life.